'''Roald Amundsen''' o [[Norgagh|norgaghek]] [[hwithrer]] a fogellas orth [[ayredh penneghlek|pennow-aghel]]. Ev a hembronkas an kynsa [[vyaj hwithra]] dhe dhrehedhes an [[Penn-Aghel an Soth]] ha'n kynsa a allas previ y trehedhas an [[Penn-Aghel an North]]. Amundsen o ynwedh an kynsa den the vyajya der an [[Tremen North-west]].

==Bewnans==
Pan o Amundsen yowynk, ev a erviras gul devnydh a'y vewnans dhe hwithra tiredhow gwyls. Awenys veu dre bewnansow [[Fridtjof Nansen]] ha [[John Franklin]].<ref name="Bewnans">{{devyn lyver | titel=My Life as an Explorer | dyller=Doubleday, Page & company | awtor=Amundsen, Roald | bledhen=1927 | le=Garden City, NY}}</ref> Ha'y vamm o byw ny wrug ev mos dhe'n mor, dell ambosas ev dhedhi. Awos hy mernans, ev a asas an bennskol ha dalleth hwithra an bys pan o va 21 bloodh.While his mother was alive he did not go to sea, to keep a promise to her. After her death, he quit university to begin exploring the world at 21 years old.<ref name="Thomas">{{devyn lyver |diwettha=Thomas |kynsa=Henry |awtor2=Dana Lee Thomas |bledhen=1972 |titel=Living Adventures in Science |dyller=Ayer Publishing |folennow=196–201 |isbn=978-0-8369-2573-9 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FFXyKIa_-vgC}}</ref>

Yn 1897, ev eth gans [[Vyaj Hwithra Belg Antarktek]] avel kynsa brennyas. Hemm o an kynsa vyaj dhe wortos der an Gwav orth Antarktek, wosa bos agan lester stag yn rew ma ny alsons diberth.

Yn 1903, Amundsen a hembronkas an kynsa vyaj hwithra dhe dhreusi [[Tremen North-west]].<ref name="hwithra">{{devyn lyver|titel=''Roald Amundsen and the Exploration of the Northwest Passage''|dyller=Gwithti Fram |le=Oslo|bledhen=2008|isbn=9788282350013|folennow=63–65}}</ref>

Yn mis Hedra, 1911, ev a dhallathas y vyaj dhe Antarktek, peswar gour erel ganso, yn assay a vos an kynsa den dhe dhrehedhes Penn-Aghel an Soth.<ref>{{devyn lyver |diwettha=Huntford |kynsa=Roland |bledhen=1985 |titel=The Last Place on Earth |dyller=Pan Books |le=London and Sydney |isbn=0-330-28816-4}}</ref>  [[Robert Falcon Scott]], hwithrer Breten Veur, a dremenas dhe Antarktek gans bagas y honan saw deg dydh war-lergh Amundsen. An dhew hwithrer a resegas war-tu ha Penn-Aghel an Soth, mes Amundsen ha'y wer a wrug devnydh a [[ski]]s ha [[kerri slynk]] [[keun]] rag treusporth. Hemm o moy effeythadow. Y'n 14ves mis Kevardhu, 1911, Amundsen a sewenas dhe dhos ha bos an kynsa den a dhrehedhas Penn-Aghel an Soth.<ref>{{devyn lyver |diwettha=Amundsen |kynsa=Roald |awtor2 = Nilsen, Thorvald |awtor3=Prestrud, Kristian |trylyer=Chater, A.G. |bledhen=1976 |bledhendherowel=1912 |titel=The South Pole: An Account of the Norwegian expedition in the ''Fram'', 1910–12 ''(Volumes I and II)'' |dyller=C. Hurst & Company |le=London |isbn=0-903983-47-8}}</ref>

Yn 1926, Amundsen ha'y wer a dhrehedhas dhe Penn-Aghel an North.<ref hanow="piwoankynsaynpennaghelannorth">{{devyn nowodhow |url=https://tierneylab.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/09/07/who-was-first-at-the-north-pole/
 |titel=Who Was First at the North Pole? |diwettha=Tierney |kynsa=John |dydh= 7ves mis Gwynngala 2009 |paper nowodhow= The New York Times |dydh = 20 March 2019 }}</ref> Three other expeditions claimed to make it before then, but their claims have not been verified. Two of them have been considered fraud.<ref name="Rawlins2000">{{cite journal| last = Rawlins| first = Dennis| dydh hedhas = mis Genver, 2000| titel = Byrd's Heroic 1926 Flight & Its Faked Last Leg| dydhlyver = DIO, the International Journal of Scientific History| issn = 1041-5440| kevrol = 10| folennow = 69–76; ynwedh folennow 54, 84–88, 99, 105| furvas = PDF| url = http://www.dioi.org/vols/wa0.pdf| dydh hedhas = 13ves, mis Gortheren, 2007}}</ref> Hemm a wrussa Amundsen ha'y wer an kynsa dhe dhrehedhes Penn-Aghel an North.

Ev a disapperyas yn mis Metheven, 1928, hag ev ow kemeres rann yn [[Helgh ha sawya|kanaseth helgh ha sawya]]. 

